description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF communication and advocacy work focused on COVID vaccination, the promotion of positive parenting and the rights of women and girls, with a focus on ending gender-based violence, both at the national and decentralized level. Communication approaches varied and included the use of digital cards,puppet theatre performances, TV programmes and non-traditional partnerships. The launch of “Bebbo” Parenting App, Learning Passport and U-Report built a good basis for further promoting key messages on positive parenting, vaccination, gender equality and youth engagement. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
